=============================================================================

4. NO OWNERSHIP OF SCRAPED CONTENT

   The authors, contributors, and maintainers of WebScraper Pro
   (collectively, "We") do NOT claim any ownership, copyright, or
   intellectual property rights over ANY data, text, images, audio, video,
   links, or other content collected using this Software (collectively,
   "Scraped Content").

   To be explicitly clear:

     a) We do NOT own the Scraped Content.
     b) We do NOT claim any rights to the Scraped Content.
     c) We do NOT license the Scraped Content.
     d) The mere act of scraping does NOT transfer any rights to Us or to
        the user performing the scraping.

5. ORIGINAL RIGHTS PRESERVED

   ALL rights, copyrights, trademarks, and intellectual property rights in
   the Scraped Content belong to, and remain with, the ORIGINAL authors,
   creators, publishers, and/or rights holders of that content.

   This includes but is not limited to:

     a) Text content — belongs to the original author(s) and/or publisher(s).
     b) Images, photographs, and artwork — belong to the original
        creator(s), photographer(s), artist(s), and/or rights holder(s).
     c) Audio and video — belong to the original creator(s), performer(s),
        producer(s), and/or rights holder(s).
     d) Software code found on web pages — belongs to the original
        developer(s) and is subject to its own license.
     e) Databases and structured data — belong to the original compiler(s)
        and may be subject to database rights.
     f) Trademarks and brand elements — belong to their respective owners.

6. USER RESPONSIBILITY

   Users of this Software are SOLELY responsible for:

     a) Ensuring they have the legal right to scrape, collect, store,
        process, and/or redistribute any content they collect.
     b) Complying with all applicable laws, including but not limited to
        copyright law, data protection regulations (GDPR, CCPA, etc.),
        computer fraud and abuse laws, and terms of service.
     c) Respecting robots.txt directives and website terms of service.
     d) Properly attributing and citing all sources (the Software provides
        automated MLA 9th and APA 7th edition citation generation to
        assist with this, but users must verify accuracy).
     e) Obtaining necessary permissions or licenses before redistributing
        any Scraped Content.
     f) Removing any Scraped Content upon request from the rights holder.

7. COMMUNITY DATASET (ray0rf1re/Site.scraped)

   The community shared dataset hosted at:
     https://huggingface.co/datasets/ray0rf1re/Site.scraped

   Is a community-contributed collection. The same principles apply:

     a) The dataset maintainer (ray0rf1re / minerofthesoal) does NOT claim
        ownership of any contributed Scraped Content.
     b) All rights remain with the original content creators.
     c) Contributors are responsible for ensuring they have the right to
        contribute the data they upload.
     d) The dataset is provided for research and educational purposes.
     e) Any rights holder may request removal of their content from the
        dataset by opening an issue on the GitHub repository.

8. CITATIONS AND ATTRIBUTION

   This Software automatically generates citations in MLA 9th and APA 7th
   edition formats. These citations:

     a) Are provided to ASSIST users in properly attributing sources.
     b) Are generated automatically and may contain errors — users MUST
        verify citation accuracy before use in academic or published work.
     c) Do NOT constitute legal permission to use the cited content.
     d) Serve as a record of provenance, not a grant of rights.

